The paper focuses on automated test generation for mobile GUI applications, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of formal specifications and reinforcement learning also suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the proposed approach also involves measuring performance and coverage, which could be related to systems and control (cs.SY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
